post_cb({"6734649": {"ViewCount": "186", "Body": "<p>I just noticed, that in N3291 a change is marked (<em>5.2.1 Subscripting [expr.sub]</em>):</p>\n<p>Before, it was ok to overload <code>operator[]</code> with the new <em>braced-init-list</em>:</p>\n<pre><code>struct X {\n    Z operator[](std::initializer_list&lt;int&gt;);\n};\nX x;\nx[{1,2,3}] = 7; // OK: meaning x.operator[]({1,2,3})\n</code></pre>\n<p>Now that is <strong>removed and replaced</strong> with:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_6734649_6734649_0\">A braced-init-list shall not be used with the built-in subscript operator.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>What was the problem?</p>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "6736025", "Title": "C++0x: Why forbid \"braced-init-list\" in \"operator[]\"?", "CreationDate": "2011-07-18T14:41:06.783", "Id": "6734649", "CommentCount": "2", "LastEditDate": "2011-10-02T10:25:25.963", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditorUserId": "34509", "LastActivityDate": "2011-10-02T10:25:25.963", "Score": "2", "OwnerUserId": "472245", "Tags": "<arrays><c++11><curly-braces><initializer-list>", "AnswerCount": "2"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_6734649_6734649_0": {"length": 4, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 5987}}, "n3337": {"so_6734649_6734649_0": {"length": 4, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 5755}}, "n4659": {"so_6734649_6734649_0": {"length": 4, "quality": 1.0, "section_id": 7487}}}, "6736025": {"Id": "6736025", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p><code>x[{1,2,3}]</code> is not the built-in <code>[]</code> operator. It invokes a user defined operator function. So take a deep breath and go on using this fun syntax. </p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2011-07-18T16:22:11.353", "CommentCount": "1", "CreationDate": "2011-07-18T16:22:11.353", "ParentId": "6734649", "Score": "9", "OwnerUserId": "34509"}, "6734980": {"Id": "6734980", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>some careful googling pointed me to <a href=\"http://www.open-std.org/jtc1/sc22/wg21/docs/papers/2011/n3236.html#798\" rel=\"nofollow\">issue 798</a>, they only <em>moved</em> it to <em>13.5.5 [over.sub]</em>, not <em>deleted</em> it.</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2011-07-18T15:03:22.497", "CommentCount": "0", "CreationDate": "2011-07-18T15:03:22.497", "ParentId": "6734649", "Score": "2", "OwnerUserId": "472245"}});